00:00:01.040 --> 00:00:03.970
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, DC.

00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:25.590
&gt;&gt; Mary-Jane Deeb: Good
afternoon, ladies and gentlemen,

00:00:25.590 --> 00:00:29.350
and welcome to the African
Middle East Division.

00:00:29.350 --> 00:00:30.650
I'm Mary-Jane Deeb.

00:00:30.650 --> 00:00:34.230
I'm Chief of the Division, and
I'm delighted to see you all here

00:00:34.230 --> 00:00:35.890
for a very special program

00:00:35.890 --> 00:00:39.520
to celebrate Jewish
American Heritage Month.

00:00:39.520 --> 00:00:43.730
Today, we're hosting Joan Nathan,
who, as our flyer points out,

00:00:43.730 --> 00:00:48.150
is a world-famous author
of 11 cookbooks.

00:00:48.150 --> 00:00:52.660
I have my own copy of Cooking
Provence - Four Generations

00:00:52.660 --> 00:00:54.550
of Recipes and Traditions.

00:00:54.550 --> 00:00:58.670
It's a fabulous book, and Joan
is well-known to all of us.

00:00:58.670 --> 00:01:01.030
She has spoken here many times.

00:01:01.030 --> 00:01:05.640 position:56%
And today, she will be talking about
her new book, King Solomon's Table -

00:01:05.640 --> 00:01:10.060
A Culinary Exploration of Jewish
Cooking from Around the World.

00:01:10.060 --> 00:01:13.440
But before that, we always
do a little commercial

00:01:13.440 --> 00:01:15.210
about our division.

00:01:15.210 --> 00:01:18.730
And as most of you already
know, our division is made

00:01:18.730 --> 00:01:23.500
up of three sections, the African,
the Near Eastern, Hebraic sections.

00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:28.510
We're responsible for materials
from 78 different countries

00:01:28.510 --> 00:01:32.370
in the Near East, Central
Asia, the [inaudible],

00:01:32.370 --> 00:01:37.620 position:56%
as well as from the entire continent
of Africa, North and Sub-Saharan.

00:01:37.620 --> 00:01:41.130
And we're very active in acquiring
and developing collections,

00:01:41.130 --> 00:01:45.790
briefing visitors coming from
all the countries of the regions,

00:01:45.790 --> 00:01:49.880
for which we are responsible.

00:01:49.880 --> 00:01:55.600
We also invite scholars and experts
who have researched and done work

00:01:55.600 --> 00:02:00.670
in our areas of responsibility,
as Joan Nathan.

00:02:00.670 --> 00:02:03.810
And she has been a
very frequent user

00:02:03.810 --> 00:02:07.290
of our collections,
which is wonderful.

00:02:07.290 --> 00:02:11.850
This is why we cherish her as
one of our very special patrons.

00:02:11.850 --> 00:02:17.550
And we do so, so that people get a
better insight and a better sense

00:02:17.550 --> 00:02:22.910
of what those countries are about,
what their culture is about,

00:02:22.910 --> 00:02:24.550
what their history is about.

00:02:24.550 --> 00:02:25.850
This is why we have these experts

00:02:25.850 --> 00:02:32.410
who make our collections come
alive in our reading room.

00:02:32.410 --> 00:02:39.720
And we certainly collect cookbooks,
and we have here the expert.

00:02:39.720 --> 00:02:43.360 position:56%
