&gt;&gt; Joan Nathan: Okay.

00:46:56.810 --> 00:46:58.110 position:56%
Well this is a really good question.

00:46:58.110 --> 00:47:01.530
What spices or what ways
of preserving things?

00:47:01.530 --> 00:47:05.950
Well, the ways were, you
know, very, very old.

00:47:05.950 --> 00:47:09.250
Salting was the primary
one, and that's why salt

00:47:09.250 --> 00:47:13.120
in a way was so precious.

00:47:13.120 --> 00:47:14.420
You could salt fish.

00:47:14.420 --> 00:47:15.720
You could salt vegetables.

00:47:15.720 --> 00:47:19.770 position:56%
You could -- vegetables, though, the
best way to preserve was in the sun.

00:47:19.770 --> 00:47:22.870
And just the way they took these
tomatoes and put them on the roof,

00:47:22.870 --> 00:47:24.820
